## Prime Directive

Correctness > speed. This system runs a live restaurant. A bad change can break ordering,
printing, and table sessions in real time.

---

## Workspace Setup

Always open via **`woosoo-platform.code-workspace`** (multi-root workspace). This keeps the
platform repo (with `docs/cases/` and `contracts/`) in scope alongside the app repo.

**Obsidian vault:** platform repo root. **Agents** refer to `docs/VAULT_INDEX.md`,
`docs/cases/CASE_REGISTRY.md`, `docs/cases/CONTRACTS_HUB.md`; use `[[wikilinks]]` in case files.
**Operators** pin `docs/cases/OPERATOR_HOME.md`. Bootstrap: `.\scripts\obsidian-bootstrap.ps1`.
Registry: `.\scripts\obsidian-case-registry.ps1` · Lint: `.\scripts\obsidian-lint.ps1`.
Guide: `docs/obsidian-setup-guide.md`.

**WSL testing (operator — do not confuse with Windows dev):** Changes land on **Windows** first;
WSL validates via **Docker from platform root** `~/projects/woosoo-platform/` (not `/mnt/e/...`).
Browser URL: **<https://192.168.100.7>** — not localhost.

| ❌ Never on WSL | ✅ Correct |
|----------------|------------|
| `composer dev` / `composer install` inside `woosoo-nexus` on the host | `./run dev` from platform root |
| Host `npm run dev` in nexus | `docker compose … exec app` or `WOOSOO_FORCE_VITE_BUILD=true … up -d --build app` |
| `http://localhost:8000` | **https://192.168.100.7** |

Host `composer` on WSL hits Windows Composer and fails (`php: not found`). See `CLAUDE.local.md § WSL commands` and `docs/cases/kds-implementation-plan.md § WSL test workflow`.

**Edit only the one active app's directory.** If you are asked to modify files in more than one
app in the same session: STOP, tell the operator, and request the task be split. Do not proceed
cross-app.

| App | You may edit |
|-----|-------------|
| Backend (Laravel 12) | `woosoo-nexus/**` |
| Frontend (Nuxt 3 PWA) | `tablet-ordering-pwa/**` |
| Print relay (Flutter) | `woosoo-print-bridge/**` |
| Platform governance | `docs/**`, `*.md` (excl. `.claude/agents/**`, `.claude/skills/**`), `hooks/**`, `state/**` |

