## Before First Edit

Complete **PRE_EDIT_GATE** (`hooks/pre-edit-gate.md`): files table, minimal patch, non-goals, risk
review. Do not edit until done. After edits, run **POST_EDIT_REVIEW** (`hooks/post-edit-review.md`),
then **hygiene gates** (below), before the case checkpoint.

---

## Hygiene Gates (mandatory on every code task)

After **POST_EDIT_REVIEW** and before the checkpoint:

1. Invoke the **`code-simplifier`** subagent on every changed file.
   - Scope: only files touched in this task, within the active app's directory.
   - Standards: apply rules from the target app's `.agents.md` (PSR-12 for nexus, Vue/Nuxt for
     tablet, Dart for bridge). Do **not** apply generic React/ESM defaults.
   - `dead-code-cleanup` runs internally as its final sub-step — no separate invocation needed.
2. Record outcomes under `## Code Simplification` in the case file.
   - If no changes were made, write `SKIPPED — no simplifications identified`.

Applies to **all code tasks** in Cursor (Tier 1–2), not just Tier 2–3.

---

## Mandatory Checkpoint (your last action)

When you finish implementing, your **last action** must be to write the Specialist checkpoint to
`docs/cases/<slug>.md` in the platform repo (it is always in scope via the multi-root workspace).

Write or update these three sections:

**`## Specialist Investigation & Implementation`** — what you investigated, what you changed, why.

**`## Code Simplification`** — what `code-simplifier` changed (or `SKIPPED — no simplifications identified`).

**`## Run State`** — refresh these fields:
```
- last_completed_agent: specialist:<agent-name>   # e.g. specialist:chuya-frontend
- next_agent: verifier
- active_runner: cursor
- status: IN_PROGRESS
- updated: <YYYY-MM-DD>
```

If you cannot locate the case file, STOP and tell the operator. Do not hand off without a checkpoint.
